<h3 id="head-ed1846afee3be21521286932b99e2aeae9e6414a"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Classes</h3>
<p>
Including: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Warrior priest (One God) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Priest (other gods) 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h3 id="head-e6791be7eed7865c6ea8fbf4d2b565ec77d74c36"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Magic</h3>
<p>
On Erna magic (fae) is an external substance that flows like liquid. Human practitioners use this earth fae and the power of their spells is dependent on the concentration of fae. Damage spells flow best downstream in the fae, and detection spells detect what is upstream. 
</p>
<p>
Spell: Sacrifice. You destroy an item and use the power to cast another spell you know. This is a low-level spell that can get really powerful with a high skill and item worth. Sacrificing cheap items is essentially useless with this spell. 
</p>
<p>
Rakh practitioners use the tidal fae, which does not flow but changes in power constantly with the time (lots of die sides), and faeborn creatures have their own innate powers. 
</p>
<p>
Some rare objects can store fae for future tapping. 
</p>
<h4 id="head-942078ca2d04f25545a316c123a392c4d5d339fd"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Special</h4>
<p>
Depending either on a virtue system or the combination of the player's class, subrace, and wisdom, faeborn creatures of varying type will appear at times near any human player character, summoned by the darkness in their subconscious. 
</p>
<p>
Coldfire should be implemented as a damage type. 
</p>
<h4 id="head-36d4b773518bffc64872b68f81d4007314d1042c"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Plot</h4>
<p>
There are several villains that need to be gotten rid off (the Hunter and the Undying Prince, just to mention the most prominent two) and an invasion to be prevented. Gradually you begin to notice the influence of Callesta behind the scenes. You need to kill Callesta to save the world, which is kind of difficult, since he regenerates from your violent thoughts. Finally you hear the terrible news: someone has named the Unnamed, and it has decided to invade Erna to cover it in eternal suffering. You are the only one who can stop it. 
</p>
